- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper offers an alternative diagrammatic representation of functional computations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the Curry-Howard isomorphism, which is relevant to some areas of machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility as the paper deals with logic and proof theory, which are relevant to some areas of AI. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper offers a new way of representing proofs and computations, which could have implications for software engineering.
